features: PLASTIC FREE : Did you know that a pack of conventional period products contains up to five plastic bags worth of plastic? We’re here to change that, with period products that are plastic free
NATURAL MATERIAL : It’s time to go back to basics. Natracare products are made from just a few simple, natural materials. No perfume, rayon or dyes and Totally Chlorine Free
CERTIFIED ORGANIC : We only use organic cotton certified to the Global Organic Textile Standard (GOTS). This means the cotton we use is healthier for you, workers and the planet
ETHICAL : Our entire supply chain, from raw materials and processing, shares in our commitment to manage and monitor resources respectfully and ethically
VEGAN : A vegan lifestyle isn’t just about food. In fact, many big period product manufacturers have a history of animal testing and poor welfare standards. We don’t
body.description: Healthier by nature. 100% Cotton. Certified organic. Non-chlorine bleached. Why organic tampons? In 1989, Natracare was developed as a direct response to health and environmental concerns about dioxin pollution by chlorine bleaching, the use of rayon in tampons, and the extensive use of pesticides on conventionally grown cotton. For over 15 years, Natracare has been trusted by women who see the good sense in making a natural choice in tampons, pads, panty liners and feminine wipes for their monthly cycle. It makes sense to choose a tampon that is made from only certified organic cotton to avoid unnecessary exposure to chemical residuals and synthetics. Natracare Organic cotton tampons and chemical free pads are high quality products made from only pure and natural materials that are not chlorine bleached and are free of rayon, plastics and synthetic materials. Made in Germany.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2010
reviews.reviewText: The only bummer is sometimes the applicator will get stuck so you have to push a little out before you insert to make sure you can. My periods have really been less of a flow since using them. Highly recommend them. If you have ever read "Gorgeously Green" they have a part in there that they add something to those non-organic tampons to make you get heavier and need them more. Stick with something that is safe and works and these do!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality and Peace of Mind
reviews.reviewText: Boxes come well packed, sealed, and in good condition. Applicator has a rounded and perforated tip, making it comfortable (although it has a moisture-barrier coating, which also makes it a teeny bit slippery--make sure your hands are dry). Comfortable and safe, good peace of mind.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars great organic product, maybe a little less absorbent than standard (i.e., mixed material, chemical-ridden) tampons
reviews.reviewText: Happy to use organic cotton in my body. The applicator is great -- cardboard, but shaped like the plastic applicators (comes to a round ending instead of the cotton sticking out of the tube). The only reason I took off a star is that I feel like its a little less absorbent than the typical store brand stuff that I used to use; granted, it had mixed materials. And it'ls not a huge deal, but I pay a lot of attention to the details. But I'm still glad to have switched to Natracare!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 16, 2012
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not sure what the difference is
reviews.reviewText: Yes, I bought tamps online...with 3 women in my home, I'd buy a whole years worth to never have to worry about running out of this pretty essential product. After researching this brand and reading about how the expanded shape is superior to the typical store brand, I was a bit disappointed that I did not notice any difference between this brand and the typical store brand I normally purchase. Note, I did not say 'the leading national brand', I said 'store brand'. I'm not so sure their claims are legit, and I'm not sure it's worth it to pay a premium for this product. While buying them online is great, again, I did not notice a difference between this brand and its store brand counterpart.
They work well and the applicators make it easier to slide in. I have never had a problem with any sort of leakage, even after eight hours.
